description:
Gomez is a 2D creature living in a 2D world. Or is he?
When the existence of a mysterious 3rd dimension is revealed to him,
Gomez is sent out on a journey that will take him to the very end of time and space.
Use your ability to navigate 3D structures from 4 distinct classic 2D perspectives.

v0.1.0.description:
Highly unstable, but sufficiently stable for initial playtesting.

Binaries can't be generated automatically on GitHub since they require data from your local game files. Do not trust anything you download from the internet. Ideally you should audit all the code in this repo, follow the build instructions in the README and generate your own files. I can't stop you though, since I am just a release note.
v0.1.0.title: v0.1.0

v0.1.1.description:
Changelog:
- Fixed some bugs and added missing anti-cubes
- Improved apworld incompatibility handling
- Added a new poster in Gomez's house

As always never trust files from the internet, but I can't stop you, I am just a release note.
v0.1.1.title: v0.1.1

v0.2.0.description:
- Fix incorrect name for Boileroom Door Unlocked
- Improve received item message (doesn't print if it's local and says the source's player rather than game)
- Split lighthouse into a lower and upper region in the apworld for the sake of better logic tracking
- Likely fixed the problem that was preventing universal tracker working
- Packaged the zip correctly for HAT this time around
- Paginated `missing` and `received` commands for ease of use

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nhyldmar/fez-ap/compare/v0.1.1...v0.2.0
v0.2.0.title: v0.2.0

v0.3.0.description:
- Improved location sending message
- Added missing boileroom map location
- Added warningif wrong save slot was likely selected
- Added custom locked doors in nature hub, tree and tree sky (currently have visual problems)
- Fixed early link door issue for sewer hub and mausoleum
- Fixed clock anti-cube exclusion based on option
- Updated README for clarity

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nhyldmar/fez-ap/compare/v0.2.0...v0.3.0
v0.3.0.title: v0.3.0

v0.4.0.description:
- Fixed various location checks either collecting early, not collectible or behind incorrect logic
- Added black monolith code to the back of the skull artifact to make it in-logic for upcoming knowledge logic option
- Fixed throne locked door not unlocking
- Swapped sleep trap with a reload trap (reloads the level)
- Added countdown message for gravity trap
- Added audio triggers when receiving items
- Added option groups and presets for web client

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nhyldmar/fez-ap/compare/v0.3.0...v0.4.0
